The paper deals with scheduling algorithms in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of Markovian models and Partially Observable Markov Decision Processes, which are topics that fall under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.MA) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
